Hi, my names kaiya and I’m 17. Im looking for advise on what I’m feeling lately, if anyone can help me. I’ve been diagnosed with depression and PTSD and I suffer from bad dissociation but lately I’ve noticed things that are frightening me. I can’t think back to anything, I’m getting small memories of things and then just blank. I don’t remember lots of my childhood, or onwards for that matter. Sometimes I’m at work washing up and then I’ll be somewhere else and hours have passed.
Sometimes I’m hearing opinions of things I’m doing in my head from voices I don’t recognise but when I look inside my head I’m stuck in a concrete room with a window at the front (my eyes). I can’t go ‘into’ my brain to put it - like memories or feelings and I’m starting to panic. I relate to a lot of what you are saying but sometimes I can’t hear anything, it’s dead quiet, sometimes for days and I think I’m making it all up. I feel like I’m going crazy. Sometimes I cry and feel overwhelmed as if I’m really upset but I don’t feel it, like me personally I’m not sad but these emotions overwhelm my body. I don’t understand and it’s scaring me. My therapist just that it wasn’t psychotic and so it is just anxiety - but this feels different. No one is taking me seriously and that makes Me scared I’m convincing myself that I’m mental ill and I’m really afraid of that. If anyone has some advise, I’d really appreciate it. :,))

maybe i'm way off but i think there are enough examples in the outside world from which to draw an understanding, to build empathy, so i do think it's called for to feel irritation or annoyance when others jump to a simplistic conclusion about the lives of others instead of the consideration they would want for their own experiences.
i as a singleton outsider understand best the coexistence of alters as maybe siblings(?) living in 1 same house nobody gets to move out from; shared experiences sometimes bring people together and sometimes are a source of constant tension, some people feel like strangers to the point you wonder how in such close quarters such a thing is possible, and of course as everybody grows and changes some dynamics stop working and new understandings have to be formed, and i imagine there's an added obstacle of balancing the secrets some people have to keep and the resentment or misundertandings that come up in the anarchy of existing outside of the outer-world social systems, like school or work, where there's a hierarchy to obay. you don't get to choose each other, but it's in everyone's best interest to make an effort to get along.
